  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, weka.classifiers.Classifier, weka.core.CapabilitiesHandler, weka.core.OptionHandler, weka.core.Randomizable, weka.core.RevisionHandler, weka.core.TechnicalInformationHandler

    public class RandomSubspaceML
extends MultilabelMetaClassifier
implements weka.core.TechnicalInformationHandler
    RandomSubspaceML.java - Downsize the attribute space and instance space randomly for each ensemble member. Basically a generalized version of Random Forests. It is computationally cheaper than EnsembleML for the same number of models.
    As used with CC in: Jesse Read, Bernhard Pfahringer, Geoff Holmes, Eibe Frank. Classifier Chains for Multi-label Classification. Machine Learning Journal. Springer. Vol. 85(3), pp 333-359. (May 2011).
    In earlier versions of Meka this class was called BaggingMLq and used Bagging procedure. Now it uses a simple ensemble cut.
    Note: The Random generator was initialised differently in versions prior to June 2014 (may affect exact reproduction of results from the above paper).
    Version:
    June 2014
    Author:
    Jesse Read
